SIMPLE: dullness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dullness
<hw>Dull"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of being dull;
slowness; stupidity; heaviness; drowsiness; bluntness; obtuseness;
dimness; want of luster; want of vividness, or of brightness.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>dulness</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And gentle <qex>dullness</qex> ever loves a joke.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dull-sighted</ent>⟦br⟧
